OL,3,CWar hero and 'huge character' Tommy
OL,4,CClough dies aged 93
OL,6,F"Tommy enrolled in the army at just 14
OL,7,Fyears old, on the very last day of
OL,8,FWWII. He joined 170 IMJIN BATTERY / 45
OL,9,FRegiment Royal Artillery and was
OL,10,Feventually posted out to Korea.
OL,12,F"Here he began his long association
OL,13,Fwith the Gloucestershire Regiment
OL,14,Fafter 170 Battery became attached at
OL,15,Fthe start of the Korean War.
OL,17,F"Conflict with North Korean guerrillas
OL,18,Fwas followed by larger battles at Hill
OL,19,F327 and of course the Battle of Imjin
OL,20,FRiver.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/5
